  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with renal impairment are usually advised to increase their fluid intake. There is
      currently, however, no evidence supporting this recommendation. In contrast,high fluid intake
      could be dangerous if urine excretion is reduced. In this study the researchers investigate
      whether increasing fluid intake from 2 to 4 litres per day has any influence on long-term
      renal outcome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
